					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Let's say a program (emulator) is placed at C:\EMU. Now, someone associates it with NES files, and click in a NES file from C:\CARTS. Since the program must read a config file, it doesn't exist at C:\CARTS, so it creates a new one, which shouldn't occur. How can I get the executable directory after launching the program?
<br />
<br /><span style="font-size: 75%; line-height: normal">(assuming Windows 7)</span></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
