						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Only problem with argv is that it's not Unicode on Windows. </div>
<br />Actually, VC++ Express that I'm using (2008 version even) creates an Unicode compatible template:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">int _tmain&#40;int argc, _TCHAR* argv&#91;&#93;&#41;<br />&#123;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;return 0;<br />&#125;</div>
<br />
<br />Since I don't need Unicode in most cases, I have to manually change that into the normal main for every console tool to keep code compatible with other compilers.</div>

					
